name: true-color-orthorectified-photomosaic-for-mesa-verde-national-park-vegetation-mapping-project
notes: As part of a 2006-2007 U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) - National Park Service (NPS) Vegetation Mapping Program to create a digital database of vegetation for Mesa Verde National Park (MEVE), a mosaic of 1:12,000-scale true-color DOQQs acquired September 15, 2003 by Horizons Inc., Rapid City, SD, was created using ERDAS Imagine Version 9.2 and LizardTech's GeoExpress 7. Processing was done for the USGS-NPS Vegetation Mapping Program and the NPS Southern Colorado Plateau Network by the USGS Fort Collins Science Center's GIS and Remote Sensing Team in 2007
